      %h3 Location: vibrant Amsterdam
      =image_tag "vibrant_amsterdam.jpg", :class=>"vibrant_amsterdam_image"
    .amsterdam_text.home_box.span3
      %p
        Amsterdam is Unseen’s home base. With its progressive galleries and renowned art academies, the city offers a fruitful foundation for the arts and thus is the ideal setting for Unseen. Amsterdam and Unseen share an international appeal, with a mentality that blends creativity, innovation and a mercantile spirit. The city stimulates an experimental atmosphere. here, conceptual thinking is second nature, it is a perfect place for the development of international creative talent. It is not without reason that nearly half the students at the city’s art institutes, like the Gerrit Rietveld Academie and the Rijksakademie, come from abroad.
    .amsterdam_text.home_box.span3
      %p
        Unseen will be held at the Westergasfabriek cultural park, a former gasworks site dating back to 1885. Its atmospheric 19th-century buildings, surrounded by a park, house a cinema, bars, restaurants and creative spaces, making it the perfect setting for Unseen. Always lively and celebrating the arts in all its forms, the Westergasfabriek is the ideal stage for Unseen’s innovative concept.      
        


